Here are some simple ways to use the terminal since you are not a student.

# First Year First Semester Student
Just press enter for courses taken, and advisor courses as well as typing no for ENGL

It will generate a course for you using benchmark courses

EX.

Enter year (e.g., 2026): 2026

Select term:
1. Spring
2. Summer
3. Fall
Enter choice (1/2/3): 3

Selected semester: 202608
Enter completed courses separated by commas (e.g., INST126,MATH115): 
Do you have classes recommended by your advisor for this semester? (yes/no): no
You have not listed ENGL391 or ENGL393. Will you be taking one of them this semester? (yes/no): no

# First Year Second Semester Student and so forth

You can use the classes generated from the first semester to generate second semester and so forth.

